The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India win by innings and 240 runs

 - Under-19 Test vs Pak 

 Piyush Chawla led from the front 

Karachi: Indian colts crushed their Pakistani counterparts by an innings and 240 runs in the second and final Test to sweep the Under-19 series 2-0 in Peshawar on Friday. 

After compiling a mammoth 611 for nine, the Indians bowled out Pakistan for 154 and 217 to complete the victory with a day to spare at the Arbab Niazi Stadium. 

Resuming at 109 for six in their first innings on the third day of the four-day match, Pakistan were done in by seamers Ishant Sharma (4-20) and Yo Mahesh (2-52), and leg-spinner captain Piyush Chawla (2-32). 

The only solid innings came from Moin-ud Din who made 53. 

In the second innings, the home side were routed by left arm spinner Shahbaz Nadeem (3-53) and Chawla (3-72) while Sumeet Sharma also took 2 for 12. 

Riaz Kail waged a valiant battle with a fighting 83 from 112 balls with 14 fours and a six. 

No. 10 batsman Raza Rehman remained unbeaten on a dour 48 from 87 balls while opener Shaan Masood made 27. 

The Indian innings was based around a sparkling 220 by Tanmay Srivastava and 146 from skipper Chawla. 

India won the first Test in Rawalpindi by 271 runs. 

The teams now play a four-match one-day series from Tuesday in Lahore. 

BRIEF SCORES 

India 611/9 decl. Pakistan 154 (Moin-ud Din 53; I. Sharma 4/20) amp; 217 (R. Kail 83; S. Nadeem 3/53, P. Chawla 3/72). India won by an innings and 240 runs. (PTI) 




